const e={de:{"search-groups":"Gruppen durchsuchen...",groups:"Gruppen","places-description":"Hier sind einige Ideen, wo du gesellig sein kannst.","swiss-tips-description":"Tips & Tricks f√ºr das Leben in Bern und in der Schweiz. Diese Tipps sind haupts√§chlich f√ºr Neuank√∂mmlinge gedacht und k√∂nnen auch f√ºr Reisende und Einheimische hilfreich sein, die vielleicht noch nicht von dem einen oder anderen geh√∂rt haben.","events-description":"Diese Events sind anders als gew√∂hnliche Veranstaltungen. W√§hrend regul√§re Events sich auf das Thema konzentrieren und Menschen oft mit ihrer Gruppe kommen, haben diese Events einen Fokus darauf, neue Leute kennenzulernen. Sie sind soziale Orte, die bewusst versuchen, Menschen zusammenzubringen und eine offene, einladende Atmosph√§re f√ºr alle zu schaffen.","logo-description":"Ein Raum zum Verbinden",description:"<strong>Ein physischer und digitaler Ort um sich in Bern zu vernetzen</strong>","groups-description":'In diesen Gruppen findet man verschiedenste Aktivit√§ten und Leute. Falls du eine Frage hast, kannst du gerne in der <a href="/groups/connect-bern" title="Connect Bern main group">Connect Bern</a> Gruppe nachfragen.',"map-title":"Digitale Karte","map-description":"Unser digitaler Raum zum Verbinden - sag Hallo zu allen, die auch da sind! Kollaboriere, arbeite, lerne neue Leute kennen oder entspanne einfach.","map-feature-1-title":"Sag Hallo","map-feature-1-desc":"Triff dich mit anderen auf der Karte und tausche dich aus.","map-feature-2-title":"Kollaboriere","map-feature-2-desc":"Arbeite zusammen an Projekten oder organisiere Events.","map-feature-3-title":"Arbeite","map-feature-3-desc":"Nutze den Raum zum Arbeiten und Lernen.","map-feature-4-title":"Entspanne","map-feature-4-desc":"Chill einfach und genie√üe die Gemeinschaft.","map-feature-5-title":"Projekt helfen","map-feature-5-desc":"Hilf beim Projekt mit und verbinde dich mit anderen.","map-feature-6-title":"Fragen stellen","map-feature-6-desc":"Hast du Fragen? Komm vorbei und finde jemanden, der dir hilft.","go-to-map":"Geh zur Karte","location-title":"Physischer Raum","location-description":"Ein gem√ºtlicher Raum in Bern mit dem alleinigen Zweck, neue Leute zu treffen und Menschen miteinander zu verbinden. Komm vorbei und triff deine Nachbarn in Bern.","location-ideas-title":"Was du bei uns machen kannst:","location-ideas":["üñ•Ô∏è Co-working und andere Leute treffen","üç¥ Zum Mittagessen vorbeikommen (bring dein Essen mit)","üí¨ Komm und plaudere","üé≤ Bring ein Kartenspiel und finde Leute zum Spielen","üí° Alles andere, was du gerne mit Menschen machst!"],"location-phone":"+41 78 316 67 27","location-contact-intro":"<strong>WhatsApp bevorzugt</strong> - wir antworten schneller!<br/> Kannst du auch anrufen, wenn es dringend ist.","location-volunteers":"Wir arbeiten freiwillig - bitte hab Geduld mit unseren Antwortzeiten! ‚ù§Ô∏è","location-btn-whatsapp":"üí¨ WhatsApp","location-btn-call":"üìû Anrufen","location-call-first":"‚ö†Ô∏è <strong>Wichtig:</strong> Schreib uns oder ruf uns zuerst an, komm nicht einfach das erste Mal unangemeldet vorbei, weil vielleicht niemand da ist. Oder, wenn du abenteuerlustig bist, tritt <a href='/map'>der Karte</a> bei und schau, ob jemand zu Hause ist!","location-process":"üè† <strong>Prozess:</strong> WhatsApp-Anruf ‚Üí Formular ausf√ºllen ‚Üí Willkommensgruppe beitreten ‚Üí Jemand best√§tigt den Termin","location-whatsapp-message":"Hi, ich w√ºrde gerne das Connect Bern Projekt besuchen!","location-visit-info":`‚òï Komm zu <a href='/events/coffee-cake-connect'><strong>"Coffee, Cake & Connect"</strong></a> jeden Sonntag um 16:00 Uhr - unsere w√∂chentliche Zeit, die speziell f√ºr neue Leute gedacht ist, die das Projekt kennenlernen m√∂chten!`,"about-title":"√úber Connect Bern","about-highlight":"Ein Raum in Bern, der sich der echten menschlichen Verbindung widmet, wo das Treffen und Sprechen mit neuen Menschen nicht unangenehm ist, sondern der Sinn dahinter.","about-p1":"Connect Bern ist f√ºr Menschen, die neue Leute kennenlernen und ihren Freundeskreis erweitern m√∂chten.","about-p1b":"Die meisten Veranstaltungen in der heutigen Gesellschaft konzentrieren sich auf das eigentliche Thema und verpassen einen sehr wichtigen Aspekt - neue Leute kennenzulernen. Die meisten Menschen gehen mit ihren Freunden zu Veranstaltungen, aber was ist, wenn du neue Leute kennenlernen m√∂chtest - warum ist es nicht sozial normal und warum f√ºhlt es sich so unangenehm an?","about-p2":"Besonders in der Schweiz, in Europa und generell in der westlichen Gesellschaft ist es schwieriger, neue Leute kennenzulernen und neue Freunde zu finden.","about-p3":"Wir sind uns bewusst, dass es viele gute Gr√ºnde gibt, warum das schwierig ist - aber wir wollen nicht aufgeben, lasst uns das gemeinsam angehen!","what-we-do-title":"Wie wir das erreichen:","what-we-do-physical-title":"Physischer Raum","what-we-do-physical-desc":"Unser Raum ist tags√ºber ge√∂ffnet, damit Menschen vorbeikommen, andere treffen und sich austauschen k√∂nnen. Ein Ort ohne Druck, einfach da zu sein und echte Verbindungen zu kn√ºpfen.","what-we-do-digital-title":"Digitaler Raum","what-we-do-digital-desc":"Unsere digitale Karte ist eine Online-Initiative, um Menschen in Bern zusammenzubringen. Auch wenn es online beginnt, k√∂nnen sich die Leute sp√§ter pers√∂nlich treffen!","what-we-do-groups-title":"Community-Gruppen","what-we-do-groups-desc":"Wir sammeln und kuratieren themenbezogene Gruppen - sowohl unsere eigenen als auch bestehende Gruppen - und heben die aktiveren und sozialeren hervor, bei denen es wirklich ums Verbinden geht. Wir m√∂chten, dass mehr Menschen diese Gemeinschaften entdecken.","what-we-do-events-title":"Veranstaltungen","what-we-do-events-desc":"Ein Ort, um Events zu finden, bei denen es wirklich darum geht, Menschen zu treffen - nicht nur allgemeine Veranstaltungen. Wir organisieren einige selbst und sammeln andere, die wir kennen. Wenn du von einem Event weisst, teile es gerne mit uns!","what-we-do-tips-title":"Sonstiges","what-we-do-tips-desc":"Ein bisschen Hilfe hier und da - zum Beispiel Schweizer Tipps und andere n√ºtzliche Informationen, damit Menschen die sch√∂nen Dinge finden k√∂nnen, die es gibt.","what-we-do-places-title":"Soziale Orte","what-we-do-places-desc":"Eine kleine Liste wirklich sozialer Orte - nicht zu kommerziell, fokussiert auf Gemeinschaft, mit vielen Events. Orte, wo man auch einfach dasitzen kann, ohne etwas konsumieren zu m√ºssen. Wir zeigen, was existiert!","about-values-title":"Was uns wichtig ist:","about-safe-space-title":"Sicherer Raum","about-safe-space-desc":"Sicherer Raum f√ºr Minderheiten - wir m√∂chten, dass sich Familien, die √§ltere Generation, LGBTQ+, Personen aus dem Ausland und Frauen in unseren R√§umen und bei den von uns organisierten Veranstaltungen sicher f√ºhlen. Wir arbeiten aktiv daran, dies zu erreichen und freuen uns sehr √ºber Vorschl√§ge, wie wir uns verbessern k√∂nnen.","about-positive-title":"Positiv bleiben","about-positive-desc":"Wir bem√ºhen uns, eine positive und einladende Umgebung f√ºr echte Verbindungen zu schaffen! Wir heissen Menschen herzlich willkommen, die ihren Freundeskreis erweitern m√∂chten, m√∂chten aber transparent sein, dass wir nicht f√ºr psychische Gesundheitsunterst√ºtzung ausgestattet sind. Wenn du mit ernsthafter Einsamkeit oder Depression zu k√§mpfen hast, ermutigen wir dich, professionelle Hilfe zu suchen - wir k√∂nnen Teil deines Unterst√ºtzungsnetzwerks sein, aber kein Ersatz f√ºr professionelle Betreuung.","about-hygiene-title":"Pers√∂nlicher Raum","about-hygiene-desc":"Komm nicht k√∂rperlich zu nah an andere heran, respektiere ihren pers√∂nlichen Raum, versuche achtsam zu sein, ob deine N√§he sie unwohl f√ºhlen l√§sst - sei es, weil sie es einfach nicht m√∂gen, Menschen physisch so nah zu sein, oder vielleicht wegen eines Geruchs. Versuchen wir, das Bewusstsein daf√ºr zu sch√§rfen!","about-boundaries-title":"Grenzen respektieren","about-boundaries-desc":"Dies ist ein Ort, um Menschen zu treffen, und die Grenze zwischen Plaudern, Extrovertiertheit, Versuchen ein Gespr√§ch aufrechtzuerhalten und Aufdringlichkeit ist sehr fein. Versuchen wir alle, uns dessen bewusst zu sein, versuchen wir, einander nicht zu verurteilen und gemeinsam zu lernen, wie man sanft zur n√§chsten Person √ºbergeht. Denk daran, Menschen zu finden, mit denen du wirklich eine Verbindung hast, ist keine leichte Aufgabe und du musst vielleicht ein paar Mal vorbeikommen, bis du endlich deine Leute findest.","about-no-dating-title":"Kein Dating-Ort","about-no-dating-desc":"Dies ist kein Ort, um Frauen anzubaggern. Leider passiert es in √∂ffentlich zug√§nglichen R√§umen, wo es weniger soziale Verantwortlichkeit gibt, dass viele M√§nner das versuchen, aber wir tolerieren das √ºberhaupt nicht. Wenn dich jemand unwohl f√ºhlen l√§sst, bring das Thema bitte zur Sprache, wenn du dich wohl genug f√ºhlst - wir werden dich unterst√ºtzen. Dies beinhaltet das Senden privater Nachrichten oder jegliche Art von unangemessenem Verhalten. Der Fokus auf Dating verdirbt es wirklich f√ºr die Frauen, sie werden bereits √ºberall sonst im Leben angemacht, lasst uns dies zu einem sicheren Raum f√ºr sie machen.","about-active-title":"Aktiv & Entwickelnd","about-active-desc":"Dieses Ziel zu erreichen ist extrem herausfordernd. Wir k√§mpfen st√§ndig damit, die Erwartungen zwischen verschiedenen Arten von Menschen in Einklang zu bringen, wir machen Fehler, lernen und wachsen. Aber wir wollen nicht aufgeben! Wir suchen Hilfe, sei es finanziell oder einfach durch deine Zeit als freiwillige Person. Bitte melde dich bei uns, um uns Ratschl√§ge zu geben, deine Meinung zu teilen, wir sind daran interessiert, besser zu werden! Wir haben auch reine Frauengruppen, falls du daran interessiert bist, dort beizutreten und zu teilen :)","support-us-title":"Wie kann ich helfen?","support-us-description":"Es gibt viele M√∂glichkeiten, wie du uns helfen kannst, unsere Vision zu erreichen, Menschen in Bern zu verbinden. Hier sind einige davon, vielen Dank f√ºrs Lesen!","support-events-title":"üéØ Hilf bei der Planung von Events","support-events-desc":"Wir haben einen Raum, um Events zu kreieren, die Menschen zusammenbringen und echte Verbindungen schaffen, und wir brauchen deine Hilfe dabei! Besuche unsere <a href='https://github.com/connectbern/events/issues' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>GitHub Event-Issues-Seite</a> um Kommentare zu schreiben, Tipps zu geben, Ideen beizutragen oder eine v√∂llig neue Event-Idee hinzuzuf√ºgen!","support-physical-title":"ü§ù Hilf bei Events vor Ort","support-physical-desc":"Du kannst auch bei Events selbst helfen: komm fr√ºher und hilf beim Aufbauen, bleib etwas l√§nger zum Aufr√§umen, hilf beim Empfang neuer Leute, teile Ideen wie wir Dinge verbessern k√∂nnen. Schon allein dein Interesse am Helfen zu zeigen, hilft sehr! Es ist enorm hilfreich, wenn wir Menschen dabei haben, die sich Zeit genommen haben, die Mission und die Vision des Projekts zu verstehen.","support-financial-title":"üíù Finanzielle Unterst√ºtzung","support-financial-desc":"Die Miete ist teuer - das ist der Hauptgrund, warum wir Geld brauchen. Wir haben einen zentralen Ort in Bern mit einem gro√üartigen Vermieter und keine Probleme mit den Nachbarn, und wir w√ºrden ihn sehr gerne behalten! Wenn du Ideen hast, wie du das Projekt finanziell unterst√ºtzen kannst, w√ºrden wir das gerne h√∂ren.","support-membership-title":"Mitgliedschaft","support-membership-desc":"Jeder ist hier willkommen, auch ohne Mitglied zu sein. Wenn du viel Zeit hier verbringst, den Raum zum Co-Working nutzt und dir 100 Franken pro Monat leisten kannst, w√§re es fantastisch, Mitglied zu werden - wir werden dich als Teil des Kernteams sehen und es hilft uns, den Raum zu erhalten.","support-donate-title":"Einmalige Spende","support-donate-desc":"Du kannst auch einfach spenden, was du kannst:","support-donate-per-event":"üíù Empfohlene Spende pro Event: <strong>CHF 20</strong>","support-donate-per-event-desc":"Jeder ist willkommen ‚Äì auch wenn du kein Geld spenden kannst. Wir glauben daran, Menschen zusammenzubringen, unabh√§ngig von ihrer finanziellen Situation. Wenn du in der Schweiz arbeitest, ist CHF 20 eine nette Spende, die uns hilft, die Kosten f√ºr Essen, Getr√§nke, Miete und Organisation zu decken. Wenn du nicht finanziell beitragen kannst, kannst du gerne deine Zeit als Freiwillige/r einbringen!","support-ways-to-donate":"So kannst du spenden:","support-twint-title":"üì± Twint","support-twint-desc":"Der einfachste Weg zu spenden mit deinem Handy:","support-twint-note":"F√ºr kleinere Betr√§ge bevorzugen wir, dass du direkt an unsere Nummer twintest, um die hohe Geb√ºhr von Twint zu vermeiden.","support-twint-number":"Unsere Twint-Nummer:","support-twint-number-value":"+41 78 316 67 27","support-btn-save-contact":"üìû Kontakt speichern","support-btn-copy-number":"Nummer kopieren","support-credit-card-title":"üí≥ Kreditkarte","support-credit-card-desc":"Spende sicher online mit deiner Kredit- oder Debitkarte:","support-btn-credit-card":"Kreditkarte","support-bank-title":"üè¶ Bank√ºberweisung (eBanking)","support-bank-desc":"Du kannst eine direkte √úberweisung auf unser Konto machen. Bitte kontaktiere uns f√ºr IBAN-Nummer und Details.","support-bank-holder":"Kontoinhaber:","support-bank-holder-value":"Chagai Friedlander","support-bank-iban":"IBAN:","support-bank-iban-value":"CH4108440258673882001","support-bank-name":"Bank:","support-bank-name-value":"Cler","support-bank-reference":"Verwendungszweck:","support-bank-reference-value":"Spende - Connect Bern","support-cash-title":"üíµ Bargeld","support-cash-desc":"Bevorzugst du pers√∂nlich zu spenden? Bargeldspenden sind immer willkommen!","support-cash-details":"Du kannst deine Spende in der daf√ºr vorgesehenen Box in unserem Raum hinterlassen. Suche nach der Spendenbox in der N√§he des Eingangs.","support-thank-you":"Danke, dass du unsere Gemeinschaft unterst√ºtzt! üôè","support-thank-you-desc":"Jeder Beitrag hilft uns, diesen Raum offen und einladend f√ºr alle zu halten.","contact-title":"Schreib uns","contact-description":"Hast du eine Frage, einen Vorschlag oder m√∂chtest du dich einfach melden?<br>F√ºlle das untenstehende Formular aus und wir melden uns so schnell wie m√∂glich bei dir!","contact-name":"Name","contact-email":"E-Mail *","contact-phone":"Telefonnummer","contact-message":"Nachricht","contact-submit":"Nachricht senden","contact-submitting":"Wird gesendet...","contact-success":"Vielen Dank! Wir melden uns bald bei dir.","contact-error":"Etwas ist schiefgelaufen. Bitte versuche es erneut.","events-suggest-title":"Weisst du von einem Event?","events-suggest-description":"Wir suchen Events, die sich auf das Kennenlernen neuer Menschen konzentrieren ‚Äì nicht nur kommerzielle oder thematisch fokussierte Veranstaltungen. Wenn das Event, von dem du weisst, Menschen zusammenbringt und eine offene, einladende Atmosph√§re schafft, w√ºrden wir gerne davon h√∂ren!","events-suggest-button":"Event vorschlagen"},en:{"search-groups":"Search groups...",groups:"Groups","swiss-tips-description":"Tips & Tricks for living in Bern and Switzerland! These tips are mainly for newcomers and might also be helpful for travelers and locals who might not have heard about a thing or two.","places-description":"Here are some ideas of where you can be social.","events-description":"These events are different from regular events. While regular events focus on the topic itself and people often come with their group, these events have a focus on meeting new people. They're social places that consciously try to bring people together and create an open, welcoming atmosphere that's accepting of everyone.","logo-description":"A space to connect",description:"<strong>A physical and digital space to connect in Bern</strong>","groups-description":'In these groups you can do many different things. If you have a general question, feel free to ask in the <a href="/groups/connect-bern" title="Connect Bern main group">Connect Bern</a> group. People will be happy to help out.',"map-title":"Digital Map","map-description":"Our digital space to connect - say hi to anyone who's also there! Collaborate, work, meet people, or just chill.","map-feature-1-title":"Say Hi","map-feature-1-desc":"Meet up with others on the map and connect.","map-feature-2-title":"Collaborate","map-feature-2-desc":"Work together on projects or organize events.","map-feature-3-title":"Work","map-feature-3-desc":"Use the space for working and learning.","map-feature-4-title":"Chill","map-feature-4-desc":"Just relax and enjoy the community.","map-feature-5-title":"Help the Project","map-feature-5-desc":"Help with the project and connect with people.","map-feature-6-title":"Ask Questions","map-feature-6-desc":"Have questions about anything? Join and find someone to help you.","go-to-map":"Go to the Map","location-title":"Physical Space","location-description":"A comfy space in Bern with the sole purpose of meeting new people and connecting between people. Come visit and meet your neighbors in Bern.","location-ideas-title":"What you can do at our place:","location-ideas":["üñ•Ô∏è Co-work and meet other people working","üç¥ Join for lunch (bring your lunch with you)","üí¨ Come and chat","üé≤ Bring a card game and find people to play","üí° Anything else you like doing with people!"],"location-phone":"+41 78 316 67 27","location-contact-intro":"<strong>WhatsApp preferred</strong> - we respond faster!<br/> You can also call if it's urgent.","location-volunteers":"We're volunteers - please be patient with our response times! ‚ù§Ô∏è","location-btn-whatsapp":"üí¨ WhatsApp","location-btn-call":"üìû Call","location-call-first":"‚ö†Ô∏è <strong>Important:</strong> Write us or call us first, don't just show up the first time unanounced because there might not be anyone there. Or, if you're feeling adventurous, join <a href='/map'>the map</a> and check if anyone is home!","location-process":"üè† <strong>Process:</strong> WhatsApp call ‚Üí Fill form ‚Üí Join welcome group ‚Üí Someone confirms they can show you around","location-whatsapp-message":"Hi, I would love to visit the Connect Bern project!","location-visit-info":`‚òï Come to <a href='/events/coffee-cake-connect'><strong>"Coffee, Cake & Connect"</strong></a> every Sunday at 4pm - our weekly time dedicated for new people who want to see what the project is about!`,"about-title":"About Connect Bern","about-highlight":"A space in Bern dedicated to genuine human connection, where meeting and talking to new people isn't awkward, it's the point.","about-p1":"Connect Bern is for people looking to meet new people and expand their friend circle.","about-p1b":"Most events in society nowadays are concentrated on the actual topic, missing a very important aspect - meeting new people. Most people go to events together with their friends, but what if you want to meet new people - why is it not socially normal and why does it feel so awkward?","about-p2":"Especially in Switzerland, in Europe and in general in western society it is more difficult to meet new people and to make new friends.","about-p3":"We are aware that there are many good reasons why this is difficult - but we don't want to give up, let's tackle this together!","what-we-do-title":"How We Achieve This:","what-we-do-physical-title":"Physical Space","what-we-do-physical-desc":"Our space is open during the day for anyone to come, meet people, and socialize. A place with no pressure, just to be present and make genuine connections.","what-we-do-digital-title":"Digital Space","what-we-do-digital-desc":"Our digital map is an online initiative to bring people together in Bern. Even if it starts online, people can meet physically later on!","what-we-do-groups-title":"Community Groups","what-we-do-groups-desc":"We gather and curate topic-specific groups - both our own and existing ones - and highlight the more active and social ones that are really about connecting. We want more people to discover these communities.","what-we-do-events-title":"Events","what-we-do-events-desc":"A place to find events that are truly about meeting people - not just general events. We organize some ourselves and gather others we know about. If you know of an event, please share it with us!","what-we-do-tips-title":"Other Things","what-we-do-tips-desc":"A little help here and there - for example Swiss tips and other useful information - so people can find the nice things that exist.","what-we-do-places-title":"Social Places","what-we-do-places-desc":"A small list of truly social places - not too commercial, focused on community, with lots of events. Places where you can just sit without having to consume anything. We're showing what exists!","about-values-title":"Things that are important to us:","about-safe-space-title":"Safe Space","about-safe-space-desc":"Safe space for minority groups - we want families, the older generation, LGBTQ+, foreigners and women to feel safe in the spaces that we have and the events that we organize. We actively work on trying to achieve that and we are more than happy for suggestions on how to improve.","about-positive-title":"Stay Positive","about-positive-desc":"We strive to create a positive and welcoming environment for making genuine connections! While we warmly welcome people looking to expand their social circle, we want to be transparent that we're not equipped to provide mental health support. If you're dealing with serious loneliness or depression, we encourage seeking professional help - we can be part of your support network, but not a replacement for professional care.","about-hygiene-title":"Personal Space","about-hygiene-desc":"Don't get too physically close to people, respect their personal space, try to be more aware if how close you are makes them feel uncomfortable - be it because they just don't like being so close to people physically or perhaps because of some odor, whether we just ate some garlic, we had to run to the bus and now we sweat, or because we smoke. Let's try to raise awareness for that!","about-boundaries-title":"Respect Boundaries","about-boundaries-desc":"This is a place to meet people and the line between chatting, being an extrovert, trying to keep up a conversation and being pushy is very fine. Let's all try to be aware of that, try not to judge each other and learn together how to continue to the next person gently. Remember, finding people you really connect with is no easy task and you might need to come a few times until you finally find your peeps.","about-no-dating-title":"Not a Dating Scene","about-no-dating-desc":"This is not a place to pick up girls. Unfortunately, in spaces open to the public, where there is less social accountability, a lot of guys attempt this, but we do not tolerate this at all. If someone makes you feel uncomfortable, please bring up the topic if you're comfortable doing so - we will support you. This includes sending private messages or any kind of inappropriate behavior. Focusing on dating really ruins it for the girls, women are already getting hit on everywhere else in life, let's keep this a safe space for them.","about-active-title":"Active & Evolving","about-active-desc":"Trying to achieve this goal is extremely challenging. We are constantly struggling with how to align expectations between different types of people, we are making mistakes, learning and growing. But we don't want to give up! We are looking for help, be it financially or just volunteering your time. Please reach out to us, to give us advice, your opinion, we are interested in getting better! We also have a women only groups if you're interested in joining that and sharing there :)","support-us-title":"How can I help?","support-us-description":"There are many ways you can help us achieve our vision of connecting people in Bern, here are a few of them, thanks so much for reading!","support-events-title":"üéØ Help With Event Planning","support-events-desc":"We have a space to create events that bring people together and foster genuine connections, and we need your help making that happen! Visit our <a href='https://github.com/connectbern/events/issues' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>GitHub event issues page</a> to write comments, give tips, contribute ideas, or add a completely new event idea!","support-physical-title":"ü§ù Help At Events","support-physical-desc":"You can also help at the events themselves: come early and help with organizing, stay a bit later to clean up, help welcoming new people, share ideas on how to improve things. Just expressing your interest in helping already goes a long way! It helps enormously when we have people around who have spent some time trying to understand the mission and the vision of the project.","support-financial-title":"üíù Financial Support","support-financial-desc":"The rent is expensive - that's the main reason we need the money. We have a central place in Bern with a great landlord and no problems with the neighbors, and we'd love to keep it! If you have ideas on how to help the project financially, we'd love to hear them.","support-membership-title":"Membership","support-membership-desc":"Everyone is welcome here, even without being a member. If you're spending a lot of time here using the space for co-working and can afford 100 francs a month, becoming a member would be amazing - we'll see you as part of the core team and it helps us keep the space.","support-donate-title":"One-Time Donation","support-donate-desc":"You can also just donate whatever you can:","support-donate-per-event":"üíù Recommended donation per event: <strong>CHF 20</strong>","support-donate-per-event-desc":"Everyone is welcome here ‚Äì even if you don't have money to donate. We believe in bringing people together regardless of their financial situation. If you're working in Switzerland, CHF 20 is a nice donation that helps us cover the costs of food, drinks, rent, and organization. If you're not able to contribute financially, you're welcome to volunteer your time to help us keep this space running!","support-ways-to-donate":"Here's how you can donate:","support-twint-title":"üì± Twint","support-twint-desc":"The easiest way to donate using your mobile phone:","support-twint-note":"For lower amounts we prefer you Twint directly to our number, to avoid the high fee from Twint.","support-twint-number":"Our Twint number:","support-twint-number-value":"+41 78 316 67 27","support-btn-save-contact":"üìû Save Contact","support-btn-copy-number":"Copy Number","support-credit-card-title":"üí≥ Credit Card","support-credit-card-desc":"Donate securely online with your credit or debit card:","support-btn-credit-card":"Credit Card","support-bank-title":"üè¶ Bank Transfer (eBANKING)","support-bank-desc":"You can make a direct bank transfer to our account. Please contact us for IBAN number and details.","support-bank-holder":"Account Holder:","support-bank-holder-value":"Chagai Friedlander","support-bank-iban":"IBAN:","support-bank-iban-value":"CH4108440258673882001","support-bank-name":"Bank:","support-bank-name-value":"Cler","support-bank-reference":"Reference:","support-bank-reference-value":"Donation - Connect Bern","support-cash-title":"üíµ Cash","support-cash-desc":"Prefer to donate in person? Cash donations are always welcome!","support-cash-details":"You can leave your donation in the designated box at our space. Look for the donation box near the entrance.","support-thank-you":"Thank you for supporting our community! üôè","support-thank-you-desc":"Every contribution helps us keep this space open and welcoming for everyone.","contact-title":"Get in touch","contact-description":"Have a question, suggestion, or just want to reach out?<br>Fill out the form below and we'll get back to you as soon as possible!","contact-name":"Name","contact-email":"Email *","contact-phone":"Phone Number","contact-message":"Message","contact-submit":"Send Message","contact-submitting":"Sending...","contact-success":"Thank you! We'll get back to you soon.","contact-error":"Something went wrong. Please try again.","events-suggest-title":"Know of an event?","events-suggest-description":"We're looking for events that focus on meeting new people ‚Äì not just commercial or topic-focused gatherings. If the event you know of brings people together and creates an open, welcoming atmosphere, we'd love to hear about it!","events-suggest-button":"Suggest an Event"}};export{e as t};
